                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d925">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15253.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State ad interim</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>793. Your 650, June 17, 6 p.m. Department today telegraphing Silliman:</p>
                <p>[Quotes Department’s telegram of June 18, 1915, 7 p.m., to Special Agent
                    Silliman.]</p>
                <p>Make similar representations to authorities in Mexico City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
